  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Advanced Gas Law Simulator\n",
        "\n",
        "This interactive notebook demonstrates:\n",
        "- Boyle's Law\n",
        "- Charles's Law\n",
        "- Ideal Gas Law\n",
        "\n",
        "Change values and observe real-time scientific plots."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Z_EaHlKE77WS"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import ipywidgets as widgets\n",
        "\n",
        "R = 0.0821  # Ideal gas constant\n",
        "\n",
        "def gas_law_simulator(law, P=1.0, V=1.0, T=300.0, n=1.0):\n",
        "\n",
        "    if law == \"Boyle's Law (P vs V)\":\n",
        "        V_values = np.linspace(0.5, 10, 100)\n",
        "        P_values = (n * R * T) / V_values\n",
        "\n",
        "        plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n",
        "        plt.plot(V_values, P_values)\n",
        "        plt.xlabel(\"Volume (L)\")\n",
        "        plt.ylabel(\"Pressure (atm)\")\n",
        "        plt.title(\"Boyle's Law: Pressure vs Volume\")\n",
        "        plt.grid(True)\n",
        "        plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    elif law == \"Charles's Law (V vs T)\":\n",
        "        T_values = np.linspace(100, 600, 100)\n",
        "        V_values = (n * R * T_values) / P\n",
        "\n",
        "        plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n",
        "        plt.plot(T_values, V_values)\n",
        "        plt.xlabel(\"Temperature (K)\")\n",
        "        plt.ylabel(\"Volume (L)\")\n",
        "        plt.title(\"Charles's Law: Volume vs Temperature\")\n",
        "        plt.grid(True)\n",
        "        plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    elif law == \"Ideal Gas Law Calculator\":\n",
        "        result = (n * R * T) / V\n",
        "        print(f\"Calculated Pressure using Ideal Gas Law: {result:.2f} atm\")\n",
        "\n",
        "widgets.interact(\n",
        "    gas_law_simulator,\n",
        "    law=[\"Boyle's Law (P vs V)\", \"Charles's Law (V vs T)\", \"Ideal Gas Law Calculator\"],\n",

        "    V=widgets.FloatSlider(value=1.0, min=0.5, max=5.0, step=0.1),\n",
        "    T=widgets.FloatSlider(value=300.0, min=100.0, max=600.0, step=10),\n",
        "    n=widgets.FloatSlider(value=1.0, min=0.1, max=5.0, step=0.1)\n",
        ")"
